-- Congo Issues Contracts for Lake Albert Oil Blocks to South African Firms
-- Michael J. Kavanagh
-- 2010-06-24T14:28:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/congo-issues-contracts-for-lake-albert-oil-blocks-to-south-african-firms.html

          
          
             Democratic Republic of Congo issued
contracts for two oil blocks in the Lake Albert region to two
South African companies.  
 Caprikat Ltd. and Foxwhelp Ltd., both owned by Aurora
Empowerment Systems Ltd. Chairman Khulubuse Zuma, the nephew of
South African President Jacob Zuma, signed a contract with the
central African nationâ€™s government for Blocks I and II in Lake
Albert, Caprikat said in an e-mailed statement today.  
 The blocks are located in the Albert Basin in the Western
Rift Valley of East Africa on the border with Uganda.   
